* politics, media, money affect each other much; often groups in these areas cooperate as if they were different divisions of the same firm; shortly : media creates political popularity, media is best created from money [or using the state media], money is got most easily via friends in the political elite
* the connections
	* media affects ruling
		* most people do not recognize when the media influences it instead of informing it; people usually vote for the candidate or political agenda that is [covertly] suggested by the media
	* ruling affects money
		# links-to internal xefzlgkrgekmxmhd
	* money buys media
	* money affects ruling
		* money often affects politics directly too; for example party  and campaign support, private political advertisements in the media, awesome [often fake] jobs for politicians who got the eroded and for their relatives
	* ruling affects media
		* by state money
			* own propaganda of the political elite in the state media, in the name of the state
			* state advertisement [often over-priced] in the friendly media
		* by authoritarian intimidation or oppression
		* extra tax on media
			* often diguised, for example as tax of advertising
			* this make the situation of all the media firms more difficult, but the friendly media does not suffer overall because they get financial support from the state directly or cronies with money
			* the particularities of the tax are designed so that it hurts the opposition the most and the friendlies the least
